                <h4>Blocking Off Time</h4>
                    <p>Open your <a>google calendar</a>.</p>
                    <p>Click on the day you want to block time off.</p>
                    <p>A pop up box will open and ask you to fill out all the details of your new event.</p>
                    <br>
                    <img class="center" style="padding: 25px;" alt="Blocking Off Time" src="/img/calendar.png">
                    <br>
                    <p>Name your block accordingly for your own personal organization and for management as your calendar will be viewed by them as well.</p>
                    <p>Then fill out the time you need blocked off. If you are blocking off time for vacation or personal days make sure the time covers the entire duration of your shift. If you are blocking off a smaller amount of time for projects or even a break make sure you select the times accordingly.</p>
                    <p>When you have finished filling out the details be sure to click the blue Save button to save the changes you made.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col s1"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
