                <h4>Sharing your Calendar</h4>
                <p>OTo the left hand side of your calendar you will notice a small bar that says <strong>“My Calendars”</strong>. Underneath this you should see your name.</p>
                <p>When you click on the hamburger next to your name you will see a small menu pop up. Then click on <strong>“Settings and Sharing”</strong>.</p>
                <br>
                <img class="center" style="padding: 25px;" alt="Sharing Calendar" src="/img/calendar.png">
                <br>
                <p>This will open your settings, scroll down until you see the sections labeled <strong>Access Permissions and Share with Specific People</strong>.</p>
                <br>
                <img class="center" style="padding: 25px;" alt="Setting for Granting Access" src="/img/calendar.png">
                <br>
                <p>When you click ADD PEOPLE you will be able to type in your managers email and share your calendar with them. After you type in your managers email it is important to use the drop down menu under their name to change permissions. You want to select <strong>make changes and manage sharing</strong>. </p>
                <br>
                <img class="center" style="padding: 25px;" alt="Adding Manager to Calendar" src="/img/calendar.png">
                <br>


